        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1949-12-07T17:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1949-12-07T17:00:00-05:00" n="1027" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d1027">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">121.5493/12–749: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                        Second Secretary of Embassy in China</hi> (<persName type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Bacon</hi>
                    </persName>), <hi rend="italic">at Nanking</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1949-12-07T17:00:00-05:00">December 7, 1949—5 p. m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>1277. Dept Defense has requested this Dept make representations Chi Commie auths
                    obtain exit permits Gen Soule, Maj Moyer and take necessary action obtain exit
                    permits balance Army personnel Nanking, including dependents.</p>
                <p>Request info status above cases and recommendations as to further appropriate
                    action re Soule, Moyer.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Acheson</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
